## Narrative Pipeline (8 Steps)

> Function: [_do_renew_style()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#L2056)

| Step | What | AI Function | Output File |
|------|------|-------------|-------------|
| 1 | Concat all input text | — | (in-memory) |
| 2 | Detect original framework | [detect_framework()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#930-1002) | `_detection.json` |
| 3 | Extract content blueprint | [extract_blueprint()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1004-1045) | `_blueprint.json` |
| 4 | Select new framework (AI rank → user popup) | inline AI call | `_rankings.json` |
| 5 | Generate new outline | [generate_renew_outline_v2()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1194-1252) | `_renew_outline.json` |
| 6 | Audit outline | [audit_outline()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1254-1320) | `_audit.json` + `_renew_outline_audited.json` |
| 7 | Write chapters from blueprint | [write_from_blueprint()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1322-1404) | `ch_01_*.txt`, `ch_02_*.txt`, ... |
| 8 | Cross-chapter review + patch | [review_narrative_full()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1489-1533) + [patch_chapter_overlap()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1535-1585) | `_review.json` + `FULL_SCRIPT.txt` |

---

## Sequential Writing Pattern (Both Pipelines)

Chapters are written one-by-one with a **sliding context window (N-2)**:

- **Chapter 1 (hook):** No previous context
- **Chapter 2:** Context = Chapter 1
- **Chapter 3:** Context = Chapters 1-2
- **Chapter N:** Context = Chapters N-2 and N-1
- **Last chapter (end):** Context = **ALL previous chapters** (review mode only)

**Word count rules** vary by position:
- First chapter → `Open` word count range
- Last chapter → `End` word count range  
- Middle chapters → `Body` word count range
- `chapter_type` field (`hook`/[end](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1631-1686)) overrides positional logic

---

## Re-ch (Re-write Chapter) Flow

> Function: [_do_rewrite_chapter()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/ui/rewrite_style_tab.py#L1735)

For rewriting individual chapters **without** re-running the full pipeline:

1. Locates `_pipeline/` folder in the output directory
2. Loads existing `_blueprint.json` and outline (`_review_outline*.json` or `_renew_outline*.json`)
3. Parses chapter index from filename (`ch_05_xxx.txt` → index 4)
4. Builds context from adjacent chapter files (ch[i-1] + ch[i+1])
5. Calls [write_review_chapter()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#2417-2599) or [write_from_blueprint()](file:///F:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/rewriter.py#1322-1404) 
6. Overwrites the output file in-place

---

## Job Management

- `_jobs` dict: `job_id → {id, task_num, folder_name, group_path, mode, stop_event, status, progress, checked, future}`
- `_job_pool`: `ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=3)` — up to 3 folders processing simultaneously
- Stop: Single job via menu, or "Stop All"
- Retry: Resets error/stopped jobs and re-dispatches

